{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Retarget provider shims to AGENTS.md + repo-wide reference sweep + optional per-tool pointers\n\n## Why\n\nOnce `AGENTS.md` is canonical, the existing shims and scattered `CLAUDE.md` references must be\nreconciled so nothing points at stale guidance. `.codex/config.toml` currently falls back to\n`CLAUDE.md` with a comment saying it's temporary \"until the guidance is migrated\"; this story\ncompletes that migration. `.agents/rules/rebar.md` is a hand-maintained neutral distillation that\nmust not drift from the new `AGENTS.md`.\n\n## What\n\nUpdate `.codex/config.toml` for the completed migration; reconcile `.agents/rules/rebar.md` with\n`AGENTS.md`; sweep the repo's ~15 real `CLAUDE.md` references to the new structure; update the\nplan-review criteria text that names `CLAUDE.md`; and record the decision on optional per-tool\npointer files.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `.codex/config.toml`, `.agents/rules/rebar.md`, the reference updates, and the criteria-text\nupdates. Out: the root-file and template changes (their own stories). **Depends on S2 and S3**\n(already linked): the sweep runs after the canonical files exist. Rollback is a plain\n`git revert` — all edits are docs/config/text with no data migration.\n\n## Design decisions (spike-validated)\n\n- The `CLAUDE.md` → `AGENTS.md` rename breaks ZERO code: every `src/` match is either the\n  unrelated env var `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` or prose (a `_processors.py` comment, a `rebar.toml`\n  comment, two LLM review-rubric files). No `.github/workflows` reference. The real surface is\n  ~15 files (excluding the `.rebar/cache/`, `bridge_state/snapshots/`, and `docs/experiments/`\n  data corpora): CONTRIBUTING.md, README.md, CHANGELOG.md, rebar.toml, and\n  docs/{architecture,event-schema,exit-codes,api-stability,jira-sync-setup,llm-framework,\n  plan-review-criteria-guide,releasing,workflow-editor,workflow-engine}.md, adr/0043.\n- Codex reads `AGENTS.md` natively as primary, so `project_doc_fallback_filenames=[\"CLAUDE.md\"]`\n  becomes moot once `AGENTS.md` exists. **Default: keep the fallback line but update the\n  \"temporary…until migrated\" comment** (removing the line is optional and deferred).\n- **Default on per-tool pointers: do NOT add `.github/copilot-instructions.md`, `.cursor/rules`,\n  or a Gemini config in this story** — defer to a follow-up ticket; if any are added later they\n  must be pointers to `AGENTS.md`, not duplicated content.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] No un-updated `CLAUDE.md` reference remains in the real surface; each remaining hit is\n  intentionally the thin pointer file.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'CLAUDE\\.md' --glob '!CLAUDE.md' --glob '!.rebar/**' --glob '!bridge_state/**' --glob '!docs/experiments/**'` returns only intentional hits.\n- [ ] The plan-review criteria text references `AGENTS.md`, not `CLAUDE.md`.\n  - Proving: `[ \"$(rg -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md | awk -F: '{s+=$2} END{print s+0}')\" = 0 ]`\n- [ ] `.codex/config.toml` reflects the completed migration (comment updated; Codex reads AGENTS.md\n  natively).\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'AGENTS.md|migrated' .codex/config.toml`\n- [ ] `.agents/rules/rebar.md` is reconciled with `AGENTS.md` (a pointer or aligned), with no\n  drift.\n  - Proving: reviewer confirms `.agents/rules/rebar.md` matches AGENTS.md content or points at it.\n- [ ] The per-tool-pointer decision is recorded (default: defer; none added here).\n  - Proving: a comment on this ticket records the decision.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` pass and the module-size CI gate is green.\n  - Proving: `make lint && make test`"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784234395093638001,"uuid":"8b59d604-8681-4fe6-806b-cddac45b8ed3"}